text: Spawn eggs originally used a single texture, which was then colored as a whole with a randomly-generated color.
Spawn eggs now use two textures, a base and an overlay, which are colored individually with values defined in the code.
Spawn egg colors were generated randomly; see #Before 12w01a for more information.
Spawn egg colors are no longer generated randomly; colors are now instead explicitly defined for each mob.
As such, spawn eggs for which no colors have been defined will simply use the raw textures directly with no further colors applied.
The colors defined for spawn eggs which are intended to be used are as follows:
Added bat and witch spawn eggs.
Added polar bear, wither skeleton, stray, husk, elder guardian, cat, donkey, mule, skeleton horse and zombie horse spawn eggs.
Spawn eggs for wither skeletons, strays, husks, elder guadians, cats, donkeys, mules, skeleton horses and zombie horses have been removed; as such, the color values no longer exist.

Spawn eggs for wither skeletons, strays, husks, elder guadians, donkeys, mules, skeleton horses and zombie horses have been reimplemented with the same color values they had previously.[verify] The cat spawn egg is still yet to be readded, however.
Added evoker, llama, vex and vindicator spawn eggs.

As spawn eggs now have separate IDs, those not corresponding to usual mobs are now deleted if loaded from this version up to 18w16a, or converted to pig spawn eggs with NBT from 18w19a onwards; as such, the uncolored spawn egg no longer appears in-game.
Added phantom and turtle spawn eggs.
Added cod, salmon and pufferfish spawn eggs.
The colors used by phantom spawn eggs have changed.
Added panda, pillager and ravager spawn eggs.
Cat spawn eggs have been reimplemented with a new color scheme.
Added trader llama and wandering trader spawn eggs.
The colors used by bee spawn eggs have changed.
Added hoglin spawn eggs - currently these use the same colors as the zombie pigman spawn egg.
The colors used by hoglin spawn eggs have changed.
Added frog and tadpole spawn eggs.
The warden spawn egg is not present in this branch.
Reimplemented the warden spawn egg with the same two colors as in the experimental snapshot.
Added hoglin and piglin spawn eggs.
Added strider and zoglin spawn eggs.
The colors used by hoglin and piglin spawn eggs have changed.
The colors used by goat spawn eggs have changed.
Added frog and tadpole spawn eggs.
Added chicken, cow, pig and sheep spawn eggs.
Added creeper, enderman, mooshroom, silverfish, skeleton, slime, spider, wolf, zombie and zombie pigman spawn eggs.
Added bat, cave spider, ghast, magma cube and squid spawn eggs.
Added blaze, ocelot and (old) zombie villager spawn eggs.
Added donkey, horse, husk, mule, skeleton, stray, wither skeleton and zombie horse spawn eggs.

Spawn eggs which do not use colors

in Bedrock and Education editions, not all spawn eggs utilize the color system, and instead use predefined sprites which are themselves colored. These may appear identical to their Java Edition counterparts, or entirely different. Such cases are listed here for the sake of completion, and to distinguish them from color-using spawn eggs via highlighting what eggs do not.

Prior to Java Edition 12w01a, spawn eggs used a single texture which was colored with a single color. This color was generated by the game via an equation, rather than specific colors picked for each egg; as such, even the unused spawn eggs had colors associated with them. There are a total of 64 distinct spawn egg colors which can be generated, and the pattern of colors repeats every 256 metadata values (such that a spawn egg with metadata value 0 will look identical to that of one of value 256, and that to one of 512, and so on).
